+//! **THREE-stage heterogeneous ExpandA recursion chain** — the C-P6 soundness wire, end to end.
+//!
+//! ## Upgrade over `expanda_crossleg`
+//!
+//! `expanda_crossleg.rs` (commit e81392d) proved a **2-leg** binding: a recursion circuit
+//! verifies two batch-STARK proofs — **Leg S** (`ShakeThreadedAir`, SHAKE128, 6665×256, real
+//! libcrux seed-5 ρ) and **Leg B** (`BindAir` l=1, 27×512) — and ties `Leg-S squeeze-output
+//! publics == Leg-B stream-input publics` (960 bytes) in-circuit via `cb.sub` + `cb.assert_zero`.
+//! This example chains a **THIRD real stage — Leg M** onto that binding, so the full ExpandA
+//! relation `SHAKE(ρ) → squeeze stream → pi_stream → rejection-sampled Â` is composed as ONE
+//! recursion tree over THREE HETEROGENEOUS gadgets (a Keccak sponge, a byte-recomposition binder,
+//! and a rejection-sample/one-hot-placement sampler) — not just two SHAKE-family legs.
+//!
+//! **Leg M — the ExpandA placement core** of `docs/bench/plonky3-shield-air/expanda_matvec_air.rs`
+//! (composition-manifest item (iii)): consumes `pi_stream` (the 3-byte candidate packs), runs the
+//! VERBATIM rejection gadget (`t = b0+256·b1+65536·(b2&0x7F)`; accept iff `t<q` via the sound
+//! lt-comparator `t − q + lt·2²⁴ = diff`, `diff` 24-bit range-checked), the VERBATIM one-hot
+//! placement (`sel` boolean, `Σ sel = place`, `Σ k·sel = cnt·place`, `place = lt·act`,
+//! `act = [cnt<N]` via the exact nonzero test), the VERBATIM A-bank write-xor-thread threading,
+//! and reads out the placed `Â` poly to OUTPUT publics via the VERBATIM factored coefficient
+//! one-hot. Exposes `pi_stream` as INPUT publics and the placed `Â` as OUTPUT publics.
+//!
+//! ## STEP 0 scope decision — REDUCED-BUT-REAL matvec (l=1, N=64, C=320 kept)
+//!
+//! The FULL matvec (l=7, 256-coeff, 4839×4096, ~20M cells, 25s standalone) is far too heavy to
+//! verify as a 3rd batch-STARK proof inside the recursion circuit on 24 GB (the 2-leg witness was
+//! already 1.33 M). Per the resource note, Leg M is a **genuinely reduced real matvec** — the
+//! SAME rejection-sample + one-hot placement + A-bank constraints, only the counts shrink:
+//!   - **l = 1** ExpandA entry (column j=0, output row i=0, nonce [0,0]).
+//!   - **N = 64** accepted coefficients (256 → 64): the placed `Â[0][0][0..64]`.
+//!   - **C = 320** candidate budget KEPT — so all 320 of Leg B's validated packs are tied
+//!     (the pi_stream tie covers the FULL Leg-B output, not a prefix).
+//! This is NOT a constant-column stand-in: the placed banks diff-test coefficient-exact against
+//! FIPS-204 ExpandA on real ρ (first 64 coeffs). The pointwise `Â∘ẑ` mults + `ĉ∘(t̂1·2^d)`
+//! accumulate (the matrix-vector *arithmetic*, PI_Z/PI_T1/PI_C/PI_OUT) are the heavy tail that
+//! completes `Â → ŵ_i`; they are DEFERRED (see docs §7.1). What ships completes the ExpandA
+//! relation itself: `ρ → Â`.
+//!
+//! ## Format decision (as in `expanda_crossleg`)
+//! Each leg is a **single-instance batch-STARK proof** (`prove_batch`): AIR eval / trace / prep /
+//! public layout / witness IDENTICAL to the shipped uni-stark air, only the harness differs.
+//! Field re-cast BabyBear → KoalaBear (AIRs are generic over `PrimeField64`). Leg M uses the
+//! DEFAULT `preprocessed_next_row_columns` (open all at zeta+zeta_next) — the batch-STARK
+//! recursion requires it; the eval reads only the current preprocessed row.
+//!
+//! ## Two cross-stage ties, one outer proof
+//!   - **Tie 1** (S↔B): `Leg-S squeeze-output publics[34+b] == Leg-B stream-input publics[b]`,
+//!     b ∈ 0..960 (the 960 squeeze bytes).
+//!   - **Tie 2** (B↔M): `Leg-B pi_stream-output publics[960+r] == Leg-M pi_stream-input
+//!     publics[r]`, r ∈ 0..320 (the 320 packed candidates).
+//! Both via `cb.sub` + `cb.assert_zero` (each public read once — a direct `connect` breaks the
+//! Public-table LogUp). All THREE proofs verified in ONE recursion circuit → ONE outer proof.
+//!
+//! ## Cases (all in one run)
+//!   1. HONEST   (S(0,0) ∘ B(0,0-stream) ∘ M(0,0-stream), both ties) -> outer prove+verify OK.
+//!   2. NEG1 (pi_stream mismatch, PRIMARY): M built over the DIFFERENT nonce-[1,0] stream, so
+//!      Leg-B packs ≠ Leg-M packs -> Tie 2 fails -> REJECTS at prove (WitnessConflict).
+//!   3. NEG2 (S↔B still rejects): B and M both over nonce [1,0] (Tie 2 holds) but S over [0,0],
+//!      so Tie 1 fails -> REJECTS at prove.
+//!
+//! ## Real-leg faithfulness gates (host, before proving)
+//!   - Leg S squeeze bytes == `tiny_keccak` SHAKE128(ρ‖[j,i]) byte-for-byte (independent XOF).
+//!   - rejection-sampled `pi_stream` == FIPS-204 incremental ExpandA reference, coefficient-exact.
+//!   - Leg B packs == byte recomposition of the squeeze bytes.
+//!   - Leg M placed `Â[0][0][0..64]` == FIPS-204 ExpandA reference (first 64 coeffs), exact.
+//!   - ρ == REAL libcrux ML-DSA-87 seed-5 ρ, re-derived by libcrux's own keygen H() step.
+//!
+//! ```bash
+//! cargo run --release --example expanda_chain3
+//! ```
+
+#[macro_use]
+mod common;
+use common::*;
+
+use core::borrow::Borrow;
+use p3_air::{Air, AirBuilder, BaseAir, WindowAccess};
+use p3_batch_stark::{BatchProof, ProverData, StarkInstance, prove_batch, verify_batch};
+use p3_circuit_prover::{AirVariant, RecomposePreprocessor, recompose_air_builders};
+use p3_field::PrimeField64;
+use p3_keccak::KeccakF;
+use p3_keccak_air::{
+    KeccakCols, NUM_KECCAK_COLS, NUM_ROUNDS, NUM_ROUNDS_MIN_1, RC, U64_LIMBS, generate_trace_rows,
+};
+use std::time::Instant;
+use tiny_keccak::{Hasher, Shake, Xof};
+
+fn main() {
+    init_logger();
+    kb::run();
+}
